m/uploads/default/original/2X/f/f76d17976d6b2c69167c10a1a18ad57e365c59be.png","https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/4/40b20273217e1b18c59bbcd3f48b6ecca758706c.png","https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/e/ed778e8997d71cec69276a0a32dbb603eb48ffc9.png","https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/4/45a3d4a0cf7fba317fc285700037318d60dfa27d.png","https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/0/0f1453d113f15d43bcedff19610229a7f75ebf60.png","https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/6/6708d8959440b8805afc8470858dfedc048bcaa7.png","https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/5/5a0098f13086eababf4f3999ed7201d14098ef6a.jpeg"]},"payload":{"url":"","schema":"20231218A","file":"content.txt","text":" C:\\OrigamProjects\\  and that your application is named  MyApplication . If you have named any of these differently, the path to your project folder will naturally differ. \n Now, let\u2019s check the initial version. \n \n \nGitBash \n To verify the initial commit, navigate to the directory where your project is located, for example, by using this command: \n  cd /c/OrigamProjects/MyApplication/\n  \n  \n\n\n[Image: https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/c/ce0ee27499f7f88bb277311c296130b74f0bf3de.png]\nDescription: The image displays a terminal interface showcasing a command line session. The prompt shows \u0022victor@HP-book-Viktor MINGW64 ~\u0022 followed by the command \u0022$ cd /OrigamProjects/MyApplication\u0022, indicating the user is navigating to a specific directory. The terminal then updates to display \u0022victor@HP-book-Viktor MINGW64 /c/OrigamProjects/MyApplication (master)\u0022, which reflects that the current directory is now set to \u0022MyApplication\u0022 and indicates the Git branch as \u0022master\u0022. The cursor is positioned at the command prompt, ready for further input.\n\n\n  \n Now check if the initial version, the initial commit, has been created: \n  git log\n  \n  \n\n\n[Image: https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/b/ba772c548716655f5e878a31896a9737547a334e.png]\nDescription: The image displays a terminal window with a command-line interface, showing a Git log for a project named \u0022MyApplication\u0022 located at the path \u0022/c/OrigamProjects/MyApplication\u0022. The user has executed the command \u0060$ git log\u0060, retrieving the commit history. The visible commit details include a unique commit hash \u00601bb3684a202aef949143eb0b7fe2419c3c4f027a\u0060, the author name \u0022Viktor \u003Cviktor.ter@advantages.cz\u003E\u0022, the commit date \u0022Thu Jan 16 13:20:40 2025 \u002B0100\u0022, and the initial commit message \u0022Initial commit\u0022. The branch is indicated as \u0022(HEAD -\u003E master)\u0022. The command prompt at the bottom shows the current working directory and indicates that the user is on the \u0022master\u0022 branch.\n\n\n  \n You can use this command anytime to view your saved commits. \n \n \n \nTortoiseGit \n In TortoiseGit, use the  Show log  option in the directory where your project is located. The log will look like this: \n  \n\n\n[Image: https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/e/e0315d9ddf72aa8f5092bd9c72cf704bcda7f2e3.png]\nDescription: This interface displays the \u0022Log Messages\u0022 section of TortoiseGit, indicating the version control history for a project located at C:\\OrigamProjects\\MyApplication. The date range is set from 1/16/2025 to 1/16/2025. The top table features a heading labeled \u0022Actions\u0022 with various control icons, while a row labeled \u0022master Initial commit\u0022 shows details such as \u0022Viktor\u0022 as the author, and \u00221/16/2025 1:20:40 PM\u0022 as the commit date. The SHA-1 hash \u00221bb3684a202aef949143eb0b7fe2419c3c4f027a\u0022 represents the commit ID, and a note indicates the initial commit\u0027s message. Below, a table lists paths, extensions, and line changes related to the commit, with \u0022Too many files to display\u0022 indicated in the lines added and removed columns. Options to refresh, view statistics, and show the whole project are available at the bottom of the interface.\n\n\n  \n \n   Tracking changes \n While developing your application, it may be useful to save versions continuously so that you can potentially revert to earlier versions. For example, you can save a new version whenever you start working or before you make any major changes. \n You can see changes not yet saved in Git by observing the object names in red in the model browser. For example, here is the new entity  Priority : \n  \n\n\n[Image: https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/4/475d2c58c37e8bc97dca9aad347c0c4ad3232fd1.png]\nDescription: The image displays a hierarchical structure within a Model Browser interface for an application named \u0022myapplication.\u0022 The structure includes headings such as \u0022Common,\u0022 \u0022Data,\u0022 \u0022Constants,\u0022 \u0022Data Structures,\u0022 and \u0022Database Data Types.","vector_provider":"AI.Ollama.OllamaTextEmbeddingGenerator","vector_generator":"__","last_update":"2026-05-01T23:39:11"},"vector":[-0.04524643,-0.006421221,-0.03747101,0.027021032,0.004995042,-0.045680963,-0.018846758,-0.02372698,-0.027763788,0.024485508,0.0016517063,-0.0466424,-0.024426611,-0.001513419,0.005500313,0.014978407,-0.0043462715,0.044328913,0.0087793935,0.033922862,-0.002039754,-0.016200338,0.06207623,0.0272047,0.004786028,0.010817111,0.004675738,-0.030247988,0.019239957,0.005870215,0.028051412,-0.038758907,0.014035131,-0.036051,-0.023655063,0.017062072,0.038980532,0.0046647037,-0.02586378,0.018941868,0.011518595,-0.030228589,-0.0035451748,0.006418588,-0.0061929743,-0.035397373,0.012332306,0.007903978,0.0029852008,-0.028232262,0.0004963788,-0.024825022,0.0021635853,-0.043962173,0.0015109729,0.072472766,-0.014990094,-0.02932151,-0.029193902,-0.014549124,-0.0064674937,0.029411772,-0.04615254,-0.027520819,-